First rewrite and cancel common factors step by step:

\[
\frac{12a^3b}{b^2}\;\cdot\;\frac{2ab^2}{9b^3}
=\frac{12a^3\;\cancel{b}}{\cancel{b^2}}\;\cdot\;\frac{2a\,b^2}{9b^3}
=\frac{12a^3}{b}\;\cdot\;\frac{2a\,b^2}{9b^3}.
\]

Now multiply numerators and denominators:

\[
\frac{12\cdot2\,a^3\cdot a\,b^2}{9\,b\cdot b^3}
=\frac{24\,a^4\,b^2}{9\,b^4}
=\frac{24}{9}\,\frac{a^4}{b^2}
=\frac{8}{3}\,\frac{a^4}{b^2}
=\frac{8a^4}{3b^2}.
\]

First write the division as a product by the reciprocal and factor everything you can:

\[
\frac{p^3+q^3}{3p^2+3pq+3q^2}\;\div\;\frac{p^2-q^2}{12}
\;=\;
\frac{p^3+q^3}{3(p^2+pq+q^2)}\;\times\;\frac{12}{p^2-q^2}.
\]

Now factor
  • \(p^3+q^3=(p+q)(p^2-pq+q^2)\),  
  • \(p^2-q^2=(p-q)(p+q)\).  

So we get
\[
\frac{(p+q)(p^2-pq+q^2)}{3(p^2+pq+q^2)}\;\times\;\frac{12}{(p-q)(p+q)}
\;=\;
\frac{12\;(p^2-pq+q^2)}{3\;(p^2+pq+q^2)\;(p-q)}
\quad(\text{cancel }p+q).
\]
Finally \(12/3=4\), so the result is
\[
\boxed{\frac{4\,(p^2-pq+q^2)}{(p-q)\,(p^2+pq+q^2)}.}
\]
